.php%3Ft%3D106205%26start%3D375%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsites%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20thing%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-models-trademarked-characters-images-study-text-phrase-prompts-2024-1%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Etools%20like%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20only%20valuable%20when%20they%20have%20access%20to%20things%20like%20news%20articles%2C%20novels%2C%20biographies%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20copyrighted%20material%20fed%20into%20their%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20at%20least%20part%20of%20OpenAI's%20defense%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20admitted%20that%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20to%20train%20today's%20leading%20AI%20models%20without%20using%20copyrighted%20materials%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20evidence%20submitted%20to%20an%20inquiry%20into%20large%20language%20models%20by%20the%20UK's%20House%20of%20Lords%20that%20was%20published%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20OpenAI%20wants%20everyone%20to%20accept%20that%20it%20had%20to%20move%20fast%20and%20break%20things%20if%20it%20was%20to%20deliver%20AI%20that%20was%20any%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20OpenAI%20is%20justifying%20its%20use%20of%20other%20content%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Altman%20has%20been%20on%20a%20charm%20offensive%20for%20some%20time.%20Last%20year%2C%20he%20held%20an%20audience%20with%20world%20leaders%20like%20France's%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20and%20South%20Korea's%20Yoon%20Suk%20Yeol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20embarked%20on%20a%20world%20tour%20to%20explain%20how%20AI%20works%2C%20why%20it%20matters%2C%20and%20how%20it%20could%20benefit%20global%20economies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-world-tour-ai-chatgpt-openai-2023-6%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E