0%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthings-to-do-in-spain-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20I%20moved%20to%20Spain%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Texas.%20Although%20I%20was%20born%20in%20Mexico%2C%20I%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20life%20living%20in%20the%20US%20so%20moving%20to%20Spain%20was%20a%20big%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20family%20decided%20we%20needed%20a%20change%2C%20we%20chose%20Spain%20because%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20natural%20fit%20%E2%80%94%20my%20grandparents%20spent%20their%20lives%20living%20between%20Spain%20and%20Mexico.%20Although%20I'm%20Mexican-American%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fraised-bilingual-grateful-family-communication-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efluent%20in%20Spanish%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20settling%20in%20Spain%20was%20initially%20difficult%20because%20my%20Spanish-speaking%20skills%20were%20rusty%20after%20living%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20started%20getting%20more%20comfortable%20in%20the%20local%20dialect%2C%20I%20felt%20more%20comfortable%20living%20in%20Spain.%20I've%20lived%20here%20for%2014%20months%20and%20I%20have%20a%20much%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20in%20Spain%20than%20I%20had%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20feel%20anxious%20when%20I%20get%20in%20a%20car%20now%20because%20I'm%20so%20used%20to%20walking%20and%20taking%20public%20transportation%20in%20Spain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20lived%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20constantly%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20sitting%20in%20traffic%20or%20relying%20on%20my%20car%20to%20get%20places%2C%20but%20in%20Spain%20I%20just%20walk%20everywhere.%20I'm%20never%20stuck%20in%20a%20car.%20It's%20not%20only%20better%20for%20the%20environment%2C%20it's%20healthier%20for%20me%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sense%20of%20community%20is%20so%20strong%20here.%20When%20I%20walk%20around%20my%20neighborhood%2C%20people%20say%20hi%20to%20each%20other%20and%20it's%20so%20lovely.%20You%20don't%20have%20that%20part%20of%20the%20day%20when%20you're%20in%20your%20car%20in%20America.%20I%20love%20being%20out%20in%20the%20world%20while%20I'm%20getting%20from%20one%20place%20to%20the%20next%20and%20not%20just%20siloed%20in%20my%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiving%20in%20Spain%20has%20shown%20me%20there's%20a%20different%20way%20to%20exist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-predicts-2030-working-culture-gen-z-millennials-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20work%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Spain.%20In%20America%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20only%20options%20were%20to%20rise%20and%20grind%20and%20get%20beat%20down%20by%20the%20machine%2C%20but%20everything%20is%20different%20here.%20In%20Spain%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20value%20their%20lives%20over%20their%20work%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20even%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-work-life-balance-advice-boss-lessons-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rd.com%2Flist%2Fcountries-with-longest-lunch-breaks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree-hour%20lunches%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drink%20a%20bottle%20of%20wine%20before%20going%20back%20to%20the%20office%20or%20they%20stop%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20afternoon%20for%20a%20leisure%20espresso%20break.%20It%20was%20kind%20of%20difficult%20to%20transition%20into%20that%20lifestyle%20because%20I%20was%20so%20used%20to%20the%20American%20way%20of%20life%20where%20work%20is%20everything.%20Even%20through%20college%2C%20I%20was%20constantly%20working%20and%20grinding%20my%20life%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20moved%20to%20Spain%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20really%20lazy.%20I%20wondered%2C%20what%20am%20I%20doing%3F%20I%20should%20be%20working%20myself%20to%20the%20bone.%20But%20then%20I%20st