02016%20or%202019%20with%20a%20surgical%20(strike)%20or%20airstrike%2C%20a%20strong%20Indian%20response%20would%20have%20entered%20the%20security%20calculus%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20served%20as%20a%20disincentive%20for%20the%20Pakistan%20army's%20support%20of%20India-focused%20militant%20groups%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20asked%20about%20this%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%2C%20who%20was%20also%20the%20principal%20secretary%20to%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20has%20been%20a%20dilemma%20for%20India%20for%20three%20decades%2C%20ever%20since%20we%20have%20started%20facing%20terrorism%2C%20and%20I%20would%20argue%20even%20from%20the%201980s.%20The%20question%20before%20India%20and%20Indian%20policymakers%20has%20been%20how%20to%20react%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20the%20argument%20I%20make%20is%20that%2C%20perhaps%2C%20in%202008%2C%20India's%20response%20was%20not%20sufficient%2C%20it%20wasn't%20adequate.%20It%20was%20over-reliant%20on%20diplomacy%20and%20not%20reliant%20enough%20on%20the%20use%20of%20hard%20power.%20I%20make%20a%20deeper%20point%20that%20India%20has%20suffered%20terrorism%20in%20the%20eighties%20in%20Punjab%20and%20then%20in%20the%2080s%20and%2090s%20in%20Kashmir.%20If%20we%20had%20crafted%20a%20response%20to%20this%20sub-conventional%20warfare%20by%20Pakistan%20even%20earlier%2C%20we%20could%20perhaps%20have%20saved%20ourselves%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20bloodshed%20and%20loss%20of%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20diplomat%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDealing%20With%20Pakistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20whether%20he%20thought%20the%20government%20at%20the%20time%20relied%20too%20much%20on%20diplomats%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%20said%20that%20would%20be%20an%20oversimplification%20and%20that%20the%20issue%20boils%20down%20to%20whether%20there%20was%20a%20capacity%20and%20the%20will%20to%20look%20beyond%20diplomacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20argument%20is%20that%20India%20now%20has%20an%20answer%20to%20Pakistan's%20sub-conventional%20warfare%2C%20as%20expressed%20in%202016%20with%20surgical%20strikes%20and%20in%202019%20with%20airstrikes%2C%20that%20it%20is%20dealing%20in%20the%20sub-conventional%20space%20where%20you%20have%2C%20you%20know%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20warfare%20or%20proxy%20warfare%20below%20the%20conventional%20realm%20of%20battle.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20is%20something%20that%20is%20going%20to%20serve%20India%20well%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20Pakistan%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20emphasised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20claims%20by%20some%20experts%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20method%20of%20dealing%20with%20Pakistan%20has%20led%20to%20a%20reduction%20in%20acts%20of%20terrorism%20in%20India%2C%20the%20former%20diplomat%20referred%20once%20again%20to%20the%20capacity%20and%20the%20will%2C%20and%20said%20both%20had%20changed.%20He%20said%20that%2C%20as%20an%20answer%20to%20Pakistan's%20terrorism%2C%20India%20decided%20to%20take%20much%20stronger%20steps%20than%20it%20had%20earlier%20in%20both%202016%20(after%20the%20attack%20on%20an%20Army%20camp%20in%20Uri)%20and%20after%20the%202019%20Pulwama%20attack.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20had%20also%20attempted%20diplomacy.%20%26quot%3B2014%20and%202015%2C%20remember%2C%20was%20a%20period%20when%20he%20engaged%20with%20Nawaz%20Sharif.%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20was%20here%20for%20his%20inauguration%2C%20for%20his%20swearing%20in%2C%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20himself%20made%20a%20visit%20to%20Pakistan%20towards%20the%20end%20of%202015.%20But%20we%20finally%20managed%20to%20craft%20a%20response%20to%20terrorism%2C%20which%20entered%20Pakistan's%20calculus%2C%20that%20this%20would%20be%20a%20cost%20that%20Pakistan%20would%20have%20to%20pay%2C%20whether%20deploying%20state%20actors%20or%20non-state%20actors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDifferent%20Approaches%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20whether%20Mr%20Modi's%20approach%20was%20different%20from%20his%20predecessors%20like%20Manmohan%20Singh%20and%20Vajpayee%2C%20the%20former%20diplomat%20said%20that%20every%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20compulsions%20of%20the%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20would%20argue%20that%2C%20in%20Prime%20Minister%20Vajpayee's%20time%2C%20he%20was%20acutely%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20had%20gone%20nuclear%20in%201998%20and%20there%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20a%20strong%20nuclear%20responsibility%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20Pakistan%20issue%20and%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20world.%20And%20what%20Prime%20Minister%20Vajpayee%20did%20was%20try%20to%20understand%20the%20nuclear%20threshold%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20red%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20principal%20secretary%20to%20PM%20Vajpayee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20feel%20that%2C%20by%202008%2C%20that%20threshold%20and%20those%20red%20lines%20were%20clearer%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20we%20perhaps%20needed%20a%20much%20stronger%20response%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20which%20led%20to%20perhaps%20more%20acts%20of%20terrorism%2C%20greater%20audacity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Pakistan.%20The%20fact%20that%20this%20government%20took%20the%20risk%20and%20took%20it%20a%20step%20forward%20and%20took%20hard%20action%20against%20terrorism%20is%20something%20that%20is%20going%20to%20stand%20India%20in%20good%20stead%20in%20dealing%20with%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E'Confidence%2C%20Not%20Aggression'%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20statement%20that%20Western%20diplomats%20have%20told%20him%20that%20the%20Indian%20counterparts%20have%20become%20very%20aggressive%20and%20that%20there%20is%20a%20great%20degree%20of%20arrogance%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%20said%20the%20change%20was%20actually%20a%20greater%20degree%20of%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20confidence%20comes%20from%20the%20confidence%20not%20just%20in%20the%20country%20and%20its%20capacity%2C%20but%20also%20its%20leadership%20and%20the%20clear%20mandates%20that%20are%20available%20to%20these%20diplomats.%20So%20now%20I%20think%20Indian%20diplomats%20have%20clearer%20mandates%20on%20what%20they%20do%20and%20say%20and%20how%20they%20interact%20with%20their%20counterparts.%20They%20do%20it%20with%20a%20greater%20degree%20of%20confidence.%20So%20I%20would%20term%20it%20confidence%20rather%20than%20use%20any%20other%20adjective%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdmiration%20Of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20videos%20emerging%20from%20the%20streets%20of%20Pakistan%20suggesting%20a%20grudging%20admiration%20of%20India%20and%20whether%20that%20was%20the%20impression%20he%20got%20before%20he%20left%20the%20country%20in%202019%2C%20the%20former%20diplomat%20said%20there%20is%20a%20change%20in%20mood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20large%20proportion%20of%20the%20population%20is%20young%20and%20younger%20people%20have%20fairly%20common%20aspirations...%20You%20would%20see%20a%20huge%20gulf%20between%20what%20the%20official%20narrative%20is%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20what%20you%20would%20capture%20on%20social%20media...%20And%2C%20certainly%2C%20%C2%A0there's%20been%20evidence%20in%20recent%20times%20of%20an%20admiration%20for%20India%20and%20questioning%20of%20their%20government%2C%20which%20has%20landed%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20kind%20of%20economic%20crisis%20it%20has%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704794460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F4fmhhfjo_ajay-bisaria_625x300_09_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-diplomats-more-confident-in-modi-era-former-envoy-to-ndtv-482885