20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c213d1c5c7b8c9a0ed54c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22723%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20gunners%20prepare%20to%20fire%20with%20a%20BM-27%20Uragan%2C%20a%20self-propelled%20220%20mm%20multiple%20rocket%20launcher%2C%20at%20a%20position%20near%20a%20frontline%20in%20Donetsk%20region%20on%20August%2027%2C%202022%2C%20amid%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20Koval's%20crewmen%20had%20served%20in%20Donbas%20in%202014%20and%20were%20used%20to%20nonstandard%20solutions%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20pulled%20out%20their%20leather%20belts%2C%26quot%3B%20Trofimov%20writes%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20fighting%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20that%20preceded%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStraining%20their%20backs%2C%20eight%20men%20using%20belts%20managed%20to%20manually%20pull%20up%20and%20load%20the%20rockets%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20book%20says%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20remaining%20elements%20of%20the%20Russian%20column%20were%20also%20%26quot%3Bturned%20into%20a%20smoldering%20wreck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20war%20story%20is%20one%20of%20many%20similar%20anecdotes%20offering%20an%20account%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20its%20up%20and%20downs%2C%20in%20%26quot%3BOur%20Enemies%20Will%20Vanish%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20title%20which%20refers%20to%20a%20line%20from%20Ukraine's%20national%20anthem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20stories%20of%20tragedy%2C%20resistance%2C%20resilience%2C%20and%20heroism.%20The%20stories%20include%20moments%20where%20determination%20saved%20the%20day%2C%20moments%20like%20this%2C%20and%20those%20where%20that%20just%20wasn't%20enough%2C%20such%20as%20in%20Buzki%20Park%20in%20Kherson%2C%20where%20the%20civilian%20volunteers%20were%20massacred%20and%20the%20bodies%20were%20ransomed%20back%20to%20shattered%20families.%20An%20overarching%20theme%20in%20the%20Trofimov's%20book%20is%20that%20for%20better%20or%20worse%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20alike%2C%20have%20been%20fighting%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20gunners%20prepare%20to%20fire%20with%20a%20BM-27%20Uragan%2C%20a%20self-propelled%20220%20mm%20multiple%20rocket%20launcher%2C%20at%20a%20position%20near%20a%20frontline%20in%20Donetsk%20region%20on%20August%2027%2C%202022%2C%20amid%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c21971c5c7b8c9a0ed5d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20gunners%20prepare%20to%20fire%20with%20a%20BM-27%20Uragan%2C%20a%20self-propelled%20220%20mm%20multiple%20rocket%20launcher%2C%20at%20a%20position%20near%20a%20frontline%20in%20Donetsk%20region%20on%20August%2027%2C%202022%2C%20amid%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Ukrainians%20proved%20that%20they%20could%2C%20against%20all%20expectations%2C%20hold%20out%20against%20the%20Russian%20threat%2C%20having%20successfully%20defeated%20the%20assault%20on%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20able%20to%20persuade%20the%20West%20to%20equip%20it%20with%20more%20firepower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20forces%20received%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHigh%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20Systems%2C%20or%20HIMARS%2C%20with%20GPS-guided%20rockets%20from%20the%20US%20in%20June%202022%2C%20roughly%20doubling%20the%20range%20of%20Ukraine's%20rocket%20artillery%20and%20boosting%20accuracy%20in%20a%20way%20that%20changed%20the%20game%20for%20artillery%20units.%20Trofimov%20writes%20the%20HIMARS%20%26quot%3Bare%20everything%20the%20Uragan%20isn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20he%20notes%2C%20the%20US-made%20weapon%20system%20auto-loads%20missile%20pods%2C%20%26quot%3Bmeaning%20that%20it%20doesn't%20require%20a%20separate%20loader%20that%20can%20break%20down%20and%20sometimes%20needs%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20eight%20men%20with%20belts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKoval's%20unit%20received%20four%20HIMARS%20and%20promptly%20began%20attacking%20Russian%20positions%20that%20were%20previously%20safe%2C%20from%20ammunition%20depots%20to%20command%20posts.%20%26quot%3BThe%20entire%20front%20line%20was%20ours%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Trofimov.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20so%20many%20targets%20everywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20units%20nighttime%20attacks%20reportedly%20led%20to%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20term%20%26quot%3BHIMARS%20o'clock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20July%2C%20the%20US%20military%20was%20openly%20praising%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20weapons%2C%20and%20a%20senior%20US%20military%20official%20told%20media%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20has%20been%20significant%20impact%20on%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20on%20the%20front%20lines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22HIMARS%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bfd160ed4f46001962fdd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22989%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20M142%20HIMARS%20launches%20a%20rocket%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20on%20May%2018%2C%202023.%3Cp%3ESerhii%20Mykhalchuk%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20later%2C%20Koval's%20unit%20played%20a%20role%20in%20the%20liberation%20of%20Kherson%2C%20a%20city%20on%20the%20Dnipro%20River%20where%20a%20land%20mine%20would%20claim%20the%20young%20unit%20commander's%20left%20leg%20but%20not%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20approaching%20two%20years%20of%20tough%20fighting.%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%20have%20paid%20in%20blood%20for%20ground.%20There%20have%20been%20steep%20casualties%2C%20significant%20equipme