t%20challenging%20external%20security%20environment%20in%20decades.%20But%20what%20is%20harder%20to%20see%2C%20is%20how%20successfully%20Bhutan%20has%20transitioned%20from%20an%20almost%20absolute%20monarchy%20into%20a%20vibrant%20and%20maturing%20democracy%20in%20the%20short%20time%20since%20its%20first%20national%20elections%20in%202008.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scale%20of%20the%20transition%20is%20hard%20to%20grasp%20easily%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20it%20is%20often%20overlooked.%20It%20was%20the%20third%20king%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20the%20dynamic%20Jigme%20Dorji%20Wangchuck%2C%20who%20established%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20National%20Assembly%20in%201953%20%E2%80%93%20barely%20a%20year%20into%20his%20reign%20from%201952%20to%201972.%20During%20this%20time%2C%20he%20transformed%20the%20country%3B%20freeing%20serfs%2C%20ushering%20in%20land%20reforms%2C%20and%20establishing%20the%20infrastructure%20that%20would%20transform%20the%20country%20from%20a%20subsistence%20economy%20to%20now%20having%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20per%20capita%20GDPs%20in%20the%20region.%20Nonetheless%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20gave%20the%20National%20Assembly%20the%20power%20to%20remove%20the%20king%20(a%20clause%20his%20son%2C%20the%20fourth%20king%2C%20would%20modify)%2C%20the%20country%20was%20an%20almost%20total%20monarchy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESalman%20Haidar%2C%20who%20served%20as%20our%20Ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201980%20to%201983%2C%20said%20that%20the%20best%20understanding%20of%20the%20Bhutanese%20monarchy%20at%20that%20time%20was%20to%20view%20it%20as%20equivalent%20to%20the%20monarchies%20in%20Shakespearean%20plays.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20in%20%5Bthe%20play%5D%20Henry%20IV%2C%20for%20the%20fourth%20king%20%5BJigme%20Singye%20Wangchuck%5D%20the%20king%20and%20the%20country%20were%20one.%20Bhutan%20was%20what%20he%20was.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20governance%20philosophy%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20the%20pledge%20that%20most%20Bhutanese%20civil%20servants%20make%2C%20is%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20loosely%20to%20the%20king%2C%20country%2C%20and%20people%2C%20as%20one%20unit.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%202013%2C%202014%2C%202015%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmo.gov.bt%2F%3Fpage_id%3D7055%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estate%20of%20the%20nation%20addresses%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20second%20elected%20Bhutanese%20prime%20minister%2C%20Tshering%20Topgay%2C%20were%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20of%20Tsa%20Wa%20Sum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20deep%20association%20with%20the%20king%20and%20governance%20is%20what%20made%20the%20democratic%20transition%20so%20hard.%20Many%20Bhutanese%20felt%20the%20king%20was%20abandoning%20them%2C%20and%20they%20trusted%20him%20more%20than%20their%20own%20choice%20of%20people%20to%20govern%20them.%20Since%20education%20standards%2C%20health%2C%20life%20expectancy%2C%20wages%2C%20and%20well-being%20had%20all%20increased%20during%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20long%20reign%20(1972-2008)%20before%20his%20abdication%20in%20favour%20of%20his%20son%2C%20the%20current%20Druk%20Gyalpo%2C%20or%20king%2C%20Jigme%20Khesar%20Wangchuck%2C%20this%20was%20understandable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20mock%20elections%2C%20held%20in%202007%2C%20to%20teach%20the%20people%20how%20to%20vote%2C%20there%20were%20four%20%E2%80%98stand-in%E2%80%99%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20Yellow%20for%20tradition%2C%20Green%20for%20sustainable%20ecology%2C%20Red%20for%20industrial%20development%2C%20and%20Blue%20for%20a%20fair%20and%20corruption-free%20society.%20Yellow%2C%20though%2C%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20the%20monarchy%20and%20monastic%20orders%2C%20and%20it%20was%20no%20surprise%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2FidUSDEL19868%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E46%20out%20of%2047%20constituencies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20voted%20for%20Yellow.%20Covering%20the%20first%20real%20elections%20in%202008%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20differentiate%20between%20the%20pledges%20of%20the%20Druk%20Phuensum%20Tshogpa%20(which%20won%20the%20elections)%20and%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Democratic%20Party.%20A%20Bhutanese%20friend%20explained%20it%20in%20the%20following%20way%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20PDP%20is%20royalist%20and%20traditionalist%2C%20and%20DPT%20is%20more%20royalist%20and%20more%20traditionalist.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20such%20things%20are%20easy%20to%20joke%20about%2C%20they%20were%20the%20principal%20hurdle%20for%20the%20democratic%20transition.%20Democracy%20is%20about%20the%20peaceful%20transition%20of%20power%2C%20based%20on%20the%20differing%20pathways%20that%20political%20parties%20offer.%20But%2C%20desperately%20afraid%20of%20criticising%20the%20royalist%20past%2C%20Bhutanese%20political%20parties%20did%20the%20opposite.%20Bhutan%20doubled%20down%20on%20what%20it%20had%20done%20in%20the%20past.%20Hydropower%2C%20which%20was%20the%20principal%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20country%2C%20was%20set%20to%20be%20expanded.%20High-end%20tourism%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20source%20of%20revenue%20and%20the%20highest%20employment%20sector%2C%20was%20expanded%20as%20well.%20The%20one%20piece%20of%20innovation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcs.org%2Fcomm_select.php%3FarticleNo%3D3963%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eminor%20outreach%20to%20China%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20first%20elected%20prime%20minister%2C%20Jigme%20Yoser%20Thinley%20%E2%80%93%20received%20such%20a%20strong%20backlash%20from%20India%2C%20that%20it%20is%20often%20seen%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailyo.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbhutan-nepal-china-india-wen-jiabao-jigme-yoeser-thinley-lpg-narendra-modi-7331%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrongly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20as%20the%20main%20reason%20for%20him%20to%20lose%20the%202013%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20overcautious%20approach%20to%20the%20past%20has%20been%20costly%20for%20Bhutan.%20In%202008%2C%20Bhutan%20pledged%20to%20increase%20its%20hydropower%20capacity%20from%201%2C480%20MW%20to%2010%2C000%20MW%20in%202020.%20It%20has%20managed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fenergy%2Fbhutan-failed-hydropower-goal-and-geopolitics-of-energy%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eonly%20increase%20it%20to%202%2C326%20MW%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20huge%20projects%20are%20over%20budget%20and%20long%20delayed%2C%20adding%20to%20huge%20economic%20strain%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20finances%2C%20since%20they%20are%20principally%20funded%20by%20loans%20from%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20had%20a%20crippling%20impact%20on%20the%20tourism%20industry%2C%20and%20a%20ham-handed%20response%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhutantoday.bt%2Fexceeds-expectations-with-over-16000-visitors-since-reopening-despite-sdf-increase%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasing%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Fee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022%20across%20all%20sectors%20did%20little%20to%20help%2C%20leading%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ttgasia.com%2F2023%2F11%2F23%2Fbhutan-tourism-looking-bright-with-reduction-of-sustainable-development-fees%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E50%25%20reduction%20of%20the%20SDF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20The%20fixation%20on%20hydropower%20(with%20few%20jobs)%20and%20an%20unclear%20vision%20on%20tourism%2C%20has%20led%20to%20an%20exacerbation%20of%20a%20youth%20unemployment%20problem%2C%20which%20a%20worrying%20trend%20of%20Bhutanese%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fbhutans-jobs-woes-drive-an-exodus-australia-2023-07-28%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emigrating%20to%20places%20like%20Australia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20And%2C%20on%20its%20border%2C%20with%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20principal%20security%20guarantor%20%E2%80%93%20unable%20or%20unwilling%20to%20manage%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fon-the-india-china-border-disengagement-is-not-resolution%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutcome%20of%20the%20Galwan%20imbroglio%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Bhutan%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chathamhouse.org%2Fpublications%2Fthe-world-today%2F2023-12%2Fchina-takes-more-land-bhutan-expected-border-deal%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincreasingly%20under%20pressure%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20accommodate%20Chinese%20claims%20on%20an%20unresolved%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-china-doklam-real-problem-bhutan%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Real%20Problem%20Lies%20in%20its%20Bhutan%20Policy%2C%20Not%20the%20Border%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20it%20would%20seem%20to%20be%20that%20democracy%20has%20not%20brought%20much%20happiness%20to%20the%20Kingdom%20which%20coined%20the%20term%20Gross%20National%20Happiness%20(GNH).%20In%20fact%2C%20given%20that%20dissatisfaction%20is%20what%20leads%20people%20to%20vote%20out%20governments%2C%20the%20Bhutanese%20have%20well%20demonstrated%20their%20unhappiness.%20Bhutan%20has%20voted%20out%20every%20party%20that%20has%20won%20power%20%E2%80%93%20the%20DPT%20in%202013%2C%20the%20PDP%20in%202018%2C%20and%20the%20last%20governing%20party%2C%20and%20the%20Druk%20Nyamrup%20Tshogpa%20(DNT)%20which%20governed%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20has%20already%20been%20knocked%20out%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20the%20current%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGNH%20as%20a%20governing%20philosophy%2C%20though%2C%20has%20never%20been%20about%20this%20type%20of%20happiness.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalip%20Mehta%2C%20who%20served%20as%20ambassador%20to%20Bhutan%20from%201995%20to%201998%2C%20was%20posted%20as%20junior%20diplomat%20in%20the%20country%20during%20the%201970s%2C%20when%20the%20fourth%20king%E2%80%99s%20term%20became%20well%20known.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20Mehta%20told%20me%2C%20the%20king%20was%20returning%20from%20an%20international%20conference%2C%20and%20was%20confronted%20by%20a%20pushy%20Indian%20journalist%20who%20asked%20him%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20rule%20a%20country%20with%20the%20lowest%20Gross%20National%20Product%20or%20GNP%20in%20the%20region.%20Irritated%2C%20the%20king%20had%20replied%20that%20it%20was%20more%20important%20that%20people%20were%20happier%20with%20the%20way%20they%20were%20going%2C%20that%20was%20the%20gross%20national%20term%20to%20be%20measured.%20Thus%2C%20GNH%20was%20born.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20frequent%20change%20in%20governing%20parties%20reveals%20the%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20solutions%20so%20far%20offered%2C%20it%20also%20reveals%20a%20deepening%20of%20democracy.%20In%20the%20first%20elections%2C%20only%20two%20parties%20qualified%20for%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20to%20run%20for%20an%20election%20a%20party%20has%20to%20have%20candidate%20from%20all%2020%20of%20its%20dzonkhags%2C%20or%20districts%2C%20of%20the%20country%20and%20all%2047%20National%20Assembly%20constituencies.%20This%20election%20there%20were%20five.%20Unlike%20the%20relatively%20empty%20slogans%20of%20earlier%20elections%2C%20now%20the%20candidates%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fseeded-candidates-present-dilemma-to-bartsham-shongphu-voters%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edetailed%20pledges%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20providing%20real%20%E2%80%93%20and%20tough%20%E2%80%93%20challenges%20for%20voters%20to%20make%20up%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20A%20journalist%20friend%20of%20mine%2C%20also%20ran%20for%20elections%20this%20year%2C%20and%20although%20her%20party%20did%20not%20make%20it%20past%20the%20first%20round%20%E2%80%93%20the%20second%20round%20has%20a%20face-off%20between%20the%20two%20leading%20parties%20if%20no%20one%20party%20gets%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share%20%E2%80%93%20the%20fact%20that%20young%2C%20idealistic%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20their%20life%20savings%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20through%20democratic%20means%20says%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20appeal%20of%20democratic%20politics%20in%20Bhutan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20hard%2C%20these%20days%2C%20to%20be%20enthused%20by%20democracy.%20The%20power%20of%20money%2C%20the%20vanity%20and%20narcissism%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20global%20wars%2C%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20trust%20that%20discussion%20and%20compromise%20can%20lead%20to%20good%20solutions.%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20story%20of%20deepening%20democracy%20becomes%20that%20much%20more%20important%20in%20this%20context.%20Against%20all%20odds%2C%20this%20country%20that%20had%20limited%20experience%20of%20elections%20and%20deliberative%20lawmaking%20except%20at%20the%20highest%20echelons%2C%20has%20embraced%20and%20committed%20itself%20to%20bettering%20itself%20through%20democratic%20means.%20Despite%20its%20many%20problems%2C%20its%20people%20have%20embraced%20a%20pathway%20that%20they%20had%20only%20once%20accepted%20reluctantly.%20Grumbling%2C%20dissatisfied%2C%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20pathway%20to%20progress%20together%2C%20in%20a%20manner%20they%20are%20(somewhat)%20happy%20with.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20can%20be%20no%20greater%20paean%20of%20praise%20to%20democracy%20or%20GNH%20both%2C%20than%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOmair%20Ahmad%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704778358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09104658%2F38483611462_4a890e6997_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20severe%20challenges%20that%20Bhutan%20faces%20%E2%80%93%20from%20its%20economy%20to%20its%20security%20%E2%80%93%20its%20stable%20and%20deepening%20democracy%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20bright%20spots%20in%20South%20Asian%20and%20global%20politics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbhutan-election-monarchy-happiness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Six%20Things%3A%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Convicts%20Being%20Sent%20Back%20to%20Prison%20Is%20a%20Verdict%20on%20Much%20More%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F20123532%2FIMG_2186.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20of%20sending%20the%20convicted%2011%20back%20to%20jail%2C%20the%20resilient%20survivor%20of%20murderous%20attempts%20and%20gang%20rapes%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20violence%2C%20Bilkis%20Bano%20has%20said%20she%20felt%20it%20was%20new%20year%20and%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftoday-i-can-breathe-again-says-bilkis-bano-after-landmark-supreme-court-judgement%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecould%20breathe%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20supreme%20court%20has%20allowed%20many%20to%20reaffirm%20their%20faith%20in%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20%E2%80%9CI%20thank%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20for%20giving%20me%2C%20my%20children%20and%20women%20everywhere%2C%20this%20vindication%20and%20hope%20in%20the%20promise%20of%20equal%20justice%20for%20all%E2%80%9D%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20other%20political%20significance%20does%20this%20landmark%20order%20have%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReminder%20of%20where%20this%20government%20stands%20on%202002%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20immediately%20brought%20back%20the%20memories%20of%20the%20other%20heinous%20crimes%20committed%20in%20the%20name%20of%20avenging%20the%20burning%20of%20the%20train%20carrying%20%3Cem%3Ekarsevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Ayodhya%20in%20the%20Sabarmati%20Express%20in%20Godhra%2C%2022%20years%20ago%20in%20February.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20chief%20minister%20was%20then%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20having%20recently%20taken%20charge.%20The%20deaths%2C%20mayhem%20and%20destruction%20under%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20watch%20put%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20politics%20on%20a%20polarised%20and%20charged%20path.%20On%20April%201%2C%202002%2C%20Justice%20(retired)%20J%20S%20Verma%2C%20then%20chairperson%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20(NHRC)%20noted%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fas-nhrc-head-justice-verma-set-the-stage-for-justice-in-2002-riots%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestigations%20in%20these%20cases%20were%20being%20%E2%80%9Cinfluenced%20by%20extraneous%20considerations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20players%20and%20recommended%20CBI%20probe%20into%20five%20cases%2C%20the%20Godhra%20carnage%2C%20killings%20at%20Gulberg%20Society%2C%20Naroda%20Patiya%2C%20Best%20Bakery%20in%20Vadodara%20and%20Sardarpura%20in%20Mehsana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReinforces%20why%20cases%20were%20shifted%20out%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20what%20has%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20spoke%20of%20fraudulent%20measures%