2https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F10133535%2F2560px-Strong_rooted_in_the_middle_of_violent_Ken-2048x1153-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Indian%20forest%20department%20gave%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fken-betwa-river-linking-push-clear-project-mp-polls-8970586%2F%5C%22%3Efinal%20clearance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20a%20project%20to%20transfer%20water%20from%20the%20Ken%20river%20as%20it%20flows%20through%20the%20state%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20the%20nearby%20Betwa%20river.%20The%20Ken-Betwa%20river%20interlink%2C%20which%20would%20involve%20damming%20the%20Ken%20and%20laying%20a%20canal%20to%20the%20Betwa%2C%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20first%20of%2030%20proposed%20river%20interlinks%20which%20would%20fundamentally%20transform%20India%E2%80%99s%20river%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20idea%20was%20conceptualised%20in%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0century%20by%20Arthur%20Cotton%2C%20a%20British%20general%20and%20irrigation%20engineer.%20Cotton%20suggested%20connecting%20all%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20major%20rivers%20to%20enable%20better%20irrigation%20and%20navigation%2C%20and%20to%20capitalise%20on%20what%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20paradoxical%20phenomenon%20of%20having%20floods%20in%20one%20part%20of%20the%20country%20while%20other%20areas%20faced%20drought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%20independence%2C%20despite%20official%20enthusiasm%20for%20large%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20including%20hydropower%20dams%2C%20this%20particular%20approach%20did%20not%20gain%20any%20significant%20traction.%20In%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressreleaseshare.aspx%3FPRID%3D1777259%5C%22%3E1980%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20Ministry%20of%20Irrigation%20(now%20subsumed%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti)%20prepared%20a%20National%20Perspective%20Plan%20(NPP)%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20transferring%20water%20from%20water%20surplus%20basins%20to%20water-deficit%20basins%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20no%20further%20government%20action%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20however%2C%20A.P.J.%20Abdul%20Kalam%2C%20who%20was%20the%20President%20of%20India%20at%20the%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnwda.gov.in%2Fcontent%2Finnerpage%2FILR-in-Supreme-Court.php%5C%22%3Emade%20a%20speech%20mentioning%20the%20subject%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Using%20the%20speech%2C%20Ranjit%20Lal%2C%20a%20senior%20lawyer%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20filed%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20in%20September%202002%2C%20and%20the%20court%20pronounced%20a%20judgement%20soon%20after%20asking%20for%20the%20project%20to%20be%20accelerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecisions%20made%20based%20on%20secret%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20came%20back%20to%20the%20subject%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F41857247%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Writ%2520Petition%2520(Civil)%2520No%2Cissue%2520of%2520networking%2520of%2520rivers.%5C%22%3Edeclared%20in%20its%20judgement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthese%20projects%20are%20in%20the%20national%20interest%2C%20as%20is%20the%20unanimous%20view%20of%20all%20experts%2C%20most%20state%20governments%20and%20particularly%2C%20the%20central%20government%E2%80%9D.%20But%20environmental%20experts%20who%20were%20consulted%20on%20the%20project%20as%20members%20of%20an%20expert%20committee%20set%20up%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20have%20regularly%20raised%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fken-betwa-interlink-means-bundelkhand-will-suffer-for-decades-to-come%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%20Interlink%20Means%20%E2%80%98Bundelkhand%20Will%20Suffer%20for%20Decades%20to%20Come%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHimanshu%20Thakkar%2C%20coordinator%20of%20the%20South%20Asia%20Network%20on%20Dams%2C%20Rivers%20and%20People%2C%20a%20network%20of%20activists%20working%20in%20the%20water%20sector%2C%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Water%20Resources%E2%80%99%20expert%20committee%20on%20river%20interlinking%20from%202009%20to%202011.%20He%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20while%20most%20of%20the%20committee%20members%20were%20government%20appointees%20who%20agreed%20with%20the%20project%2C%20independent%20experts%20like%20him%2C%20water%20management%20pioneer%20Rajendra%20Singh%20and%20watershed%20conservationist%20Vijay%20Paranjape%20often%20dissented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20issues%20for%20Thakkar%20was%20the%20use%20of%20secret%20hydrological%20data.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20asked%20for%20the%20data%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20expert%20committee%2C%20I%20was%20told%20that%20the%20Ken%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Ganges%20basin%2C%20an%20international%20basin%2C%20and%20%5Bsince%5D%20hydrology%20figures%20of%20international%20basins%20are%20a%20state%20secret%2C%20these%20cannot%20be%20made%20available%20%5Beven%20to%20the%20committee%20members%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hydrology%20data%20pertaining%20to%20the%20Ken%20basin%20and%20the%20Betwa%20basin%20is%20neither%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20nor%20has%20it%20ever%20undergone%20any%20independent%20public%20scrutiny.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20rainfall%20data%20of%20districts%20the%20Ken%20and%20the%20Betwa%20pass%20through%2C%20in%20the%20previous%20four%20years%20(2023%2C%202022%2C%202021%2C%202020)%2C%20is%20not%20appreciably%20different.%20So%20why%20has%20the%20Ken%20basin%20been%20categorised%20as%20having%20surplus%20water%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhopal%20Singh%2C%20director%20general%20of%20the%20National%20Water%20Development%20Agency%20(NWDA)%20which%20is%20entrusted%20with%20the%20river%20linking%20project%2C%20disputes%20this.%20He%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20project%20was%20based%20on%20detailed%20hydrological%20and%20simulation%20studies%20duly%C2%A0accounting%20%5Bfor%5D%20the%20upstream%2Fdownstream%20needs%2C%20environmental%20flows%2C%20etc.%2C%20in%20the%20Ken%20basin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hydrological%20studies%20were%20done%20by%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Hydrology%20(NIH)%2C%20Roorkee%2C%20and%20examined%20and%20reviewed%20by%20the%20Central%20Water%20Commission%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20added.%20The%20NWDA%20website%20carries%20a%20detailed%20project%20report%20based%20on%20a%20NIH%20study%20conducted%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-link-centre-moves-ahead-without-mandatory-latest-hydrological-study%5C%22%3E2003-04%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20study%20itself%20is%20not%20included.%20Singh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20entire%20modelling%20cannot%20be%20shared%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-no-cost-analysis-or-environment-impact-study-structures-make-way-into-project%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%3A%20No%20Cost%20Analysis%20or%20Environment%20Impact%20Study%2C%20Structures%20Make%20Way%20into%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20science%20may%20upturn%20old%20models%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20urgent%20issue%20is%20that%20science%20has%20moved%20a%20far%20pace%20from%20Cotton%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20interlinking%20rivers%20may%20be%20much%20more%20complicated%20than%20was%20appreciated%20in%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubimal%20Ghosh%2C%20institute%20chair%20professor%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Department%20of%20Civil%20Engineering%20and%20convener%20of%20the%20Interdisciplinary%20Program%20in%20Climate%20Studies%2C%20explained%20that%20atmospheric%20water%20has%20traditionally%20not%20been%20factored%20into%20consideration%20of%20water%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-41668-x%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0which%20Ghosh%20co-authored%20found%20that%20adjacent%20river%20basins%20do%20not%20exist%20in%20isolation%2C%20and%20moving%20water%20from%20one%20to%20another%20may%20have%20additional%20impact%20due%20to%20atmospheric%20water.%20The%20study%20builds%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Indian%20summer%20monsoon%2C%20when%20the%20soil%20is%20saturated%20and%20evapotranspiration%20(the%20supply%20of%20moisture%20from%20the%20land%20to%20the%20atmosphere)%20is%20fairly%20high%2C%20recycled%20precipitation%20contributes%20to%20about%2025%25%20of%20monsoon%20rainfall.%20If%20water%20from%20one%20basin%20were%20to%20be%20used%20to%20irrigate%20another%20basin%2C%20the%20combination%20of%20increased%20evapotranspiration%20and%20wind%20could%20reduce%20the%20late%20monsoonal%20rain%20by%2012%25%20in%C2%A0some%20arid%20regions%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20increase%20rainfall%20up%20to%2010%25%20in%20other%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20we%20know%20for%20certain%20that%20altering%20the%20terrestrial%20water%20cycle%20can%20impact%20atmospheric%20processes%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ghosh.%20He%20argued%20that%20there%20is%20%E2%80%9Can%20urgent%20need%20to%20include%20rigorous%20model-guided%20evaluation%20of%20hydro-meteorological%20consequences%E2%80%9D%20for%20projects%20like%20river%20interlinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Singh%20of%20the%20NWDA%20said%20that%20they%20could%20not%20comment%20on%20a%20hypothetical%20study.%20%E2%80%9CConsidering%20the%20scale%20of%20meteorological%20and%20hydrological%20cycles%20in%20the%20country%2C%20these%20inter-basin%20water%20transfers%20to%20water-short%20areas%20are%20minor%20in%20nature%20%E2%80%A6%20As%20far%20as%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20harnessed%20flood%20water%20shall%20be%20utilised%20in%20the%20Ken%20basin%20itself%20and%20some%20water%20shall%20be%20utilised%20to%20fulfil%20the%20water%20needs%20of%20other%20regions%20including%20recharge%20of%20existing%20tanks%20in%20the%20Bundelkhand%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire-300x167.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F22145316%2FKen-the-wire-1024x571.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-541835%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22669%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKen%20River.%20Photo%3A%20Dheeraj%20Mishra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20illusion%20of%20water%20surplus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20deeper%20problem%2C%20according%20to%20Thakkar%2C%20may%20be%20that%20the%20river%20basins%20classified%20as%20having%20a%20water%20surplus%20are%20only%20regarded%20as%20such%20because%20they%20are%20less%20developed.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20districts%20in%20the%20upper%20Ken%20basin%20are%20largely%20devoid%20of%20water-intensive%20agriculture%2C%20and%20with%20few%20dams%20built%20for%20storage.%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20lower%20Betwa%20runs%20through%20agricultural%20districts%20where%20water-intensive%20crops%20are%20grown%2C%20with%20a%20fair%20number%20of%20dams.%20The%20surplus%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20only%20an%20illusion%20created%20by%20the%20different%20levels%20of%20water%20utilisation%20in%20different%20geographies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20dams%20are%20sought%20to%20be%20built%20in%20the%20upper%20Betwa%20region%2C%20which%20will%20create%20a%20shortfall%20in%20the%20existing%20lower%20Betwa%20basin%20dams%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thakkar.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20shortfall%20is%20proposed%20to%20be%20rectified%20by%20water%20from%20the%20Ken%20basin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20is%20not%20only%20about%20the%20inter-basin%20transfer%20of%20water%20%E2%80%93%20the%20central%20premise%20of%20river%20interlinking%20from%20Cotton%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decisions%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20about%20conserving%20flood%20water.%20Most%20rainfall%20occurs%20in%20a%20few%20days%20during%20the%20monsoon%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20are%20hardly%20any%20flows%20in%20the%20Ken%20during%20the%20non-monsoon%20period%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20region%20is%20also%20not%20very%20rich%20in%20groundwater%20due%20to%20hard%20rock%20and%20marginal%20alluvium%20terrain.%20We%20expect%20this%20project%20to%C2%A0stabilise%20the%20availability%20of%20water%20and%20improve%20water%20management%20in%20the%20region%20particularly%20during%20drought%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20downstream%20impacts%20of%20river%20interlinking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20the%20total%20utilisation%20of%20water%20raises%20its%20own%20issues%2C%20according%20to%20Depinder%20Kapur%2C%20director%20of%20the%20water%20programme%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Science%20and%20Environment%20in%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20more%20river%20waters%20we%20use%20for%20agriculture%20and%20irrigation%20and%20urban%20consumption%2C%20the%20less%20will%20be%20left%20to%20enter%20the%20sea%2C%20especially%20in%20peninsular%20India%20where%20rivers%20aren%E2%80%99t%20fed%20by%20Himalayan%20waters%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kapur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonline.ucpress.edu%2Felementa%2Farticle%2Fdoi%2F10.1525%2Felementa.269%2F112824%2FRiver-linking-in-India-Downstream-impacts-on-water%5C%22%3E2018%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20if%20all%2030%20proposed%20river%20interlinking%20projects%20in%20the%20country%20are%20fully%20implemented%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20discharge%20by%20the%20affected%20basins%20will%20reduce%20by%2073%25.%20While%20the%20study%20focused%20on%20impacts%20to%20wetlands%20and%20estuaries%2C%20which%20would%20be%20deprived%20of%20key%20sources%20of%20water%2C%20there%20would%20also%20be%20major%20ramifications%20for%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fken-betwa-jal-shakti-secy-rejected-provisions-on-water-sharing-between-up-and-mp-citing-cost-hike%5C%22%3EKen-Betwa%20Link%3A%20Jal%20Shakti%20Secy%20Had%20Rejected%20Provisions%20on%20Water-Sharing%20Between%20UP%20and%20MP%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20fall%20in%20the%20flow%20of%20fresh%20river%20water%20into%20the%20sea%20would%20disrupt%20the%20upper%20layer%20of%20water%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%2C%20which%20is%20made%20up%20of%20low-salinity%20and%20low-density%20water%20that%20helps%20maintain%20a%20sea%20surface%20temperature%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1029%2F2000JC000679%5C%22%3Ehigher%20than%2028%20degrees%20Celsius%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20high%20surface%20temperature%20in%20turn%20creates%20low-pressure%20areas%20and%20intensifies%20monsoon%20activity%2C%20explained%C2%A0Mihir%C2%A0Shah%3Cstrong%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Edistinguished%20professor%20at%20Shiv%20Nadar%20University%20and%20former%20chair%20of%20a%20new%20National%20Water%20Policy%20drafting%20committee%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Jal%20Shakti%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRainfall%20over%20much%20of%20the%20%5BIndian%5D%20subcontinent%20is%20effectively%20controlled%20by%20this%20layer%20of%20low-salinity%20water.%20A%20disruption%20in%20this%20layer%20because%20of%20the%20massive%20damming%20proposed%20by%20the%20river%20interlinks%20%E2%80%A6%20could%20have%20serious%20long-term%20consequences%20for%20climate%20and%20rainfall%20in%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20endangering%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20a%20vast%20population.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERivers%20carry%20more%20than%20water%2C%20and%20sediment%20would%20also%20be%20held%20back%20by%20new%20dams%20built%20for%20river%20interlinking.%20This%20is%20a%20critical%20concern%20for%20the%20deltas%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Friver-basins%2Fganga%2F%5C%22%3EGanga%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Friver-basins%2Fbrahmaputra%2F%5C%22%3EBrahmaputra%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mahanadi%2C%20Godavari%2C%20Krishna%20and%20Kaveri%20basins%2C%20home%20to%20more%20than%20160%20million%20people%20who%20would%20be%20deeply%20impacted%20by%20sea%20level%20rise%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-38057-9%5C%22%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Ganga-Brahmaputra%20Delta%20found%20that%20the%20approximately%201%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20sediment%20that%20rivers%20currently%20carry%20each%20year%20would%20increase%20by%2034-60%25%20in%20the%2021st%20century%20because%20of%20more%20monsoon%20rainfall.%20More%20sediment%20in%20the%20delta%20would%20help%20to%20offset%20sea%20level%20rise%20and%20naturally%20sustain%20the%20delta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20the%202018%20study%20pointed%20out%2C%20if%20all%20dams%20involved%20in%20the%20proposed%20river%20interlinking%20projects%20are%20built%2C%20this%20sediment%20load%20would%20fall%20by%2087%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20of%20the%20NWDA%20responded%20by%20saying%20that%20sediment%20trapping%20by%20reservoirs%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20deltas%20was%20%E2%80%9Calways%20exaggerated%20without%20proper%20scientific%20study%E2%80%9D.%20While%20suggesting%20that%20such%20impacts%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cnominal%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20told%20The%20Third%20Pole%20that%20the%20NWDA%20had%20%E2%80%9Calready%20initiated%20system%20studies%20of%20the%20proposed%20link%20projects%20to%20study%20the%20likely%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20hydrology%20and%20water%20availability%2C%20demand%20patterns%2C%20surface%20and%20ground%20water%20interactions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20having%20returned%20to%20power%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20in%20the%20November%202023%20elections%2C%20and%20with%20river%20interlinking%20having%20been%20featured%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%202019%20general%20election%20manifesto%2C%20it%20seems%20likely%20that%20work%20on%20the%20Ken-Betwa%20link%20will%20be%20prioritised%20as%20evidence%20of%20the%20plan%20making%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECharu%20Bahri%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20and%20editor%20based%20in%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fnature%2Fnew-research-raises-fresh-doubts-about-indias-river-linking-plans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20The%20Third%20Pole.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704771014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F10133535%2F2560px-Strong_rooted_in_the_middle_of_violent_Ken-2048x1153-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnew-research-raises-fresh-doubts-about-indias-river-linking-plans%22%2C%